    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-27T01:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-27T01:35:00-05:00" n="622"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9131/93: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-27T10:00:00+03:25"
                            >September 27, 1937—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 27—8:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>90. Foreign Office has requested me both orally and in writing that conversations
                    regarding a trade agreement be resumed. Please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
